Package: bayesTLS
Title: Joint Bayesian 4PL Models for Thermal Load Sensitivity
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Daniel W. A.", "Noble",
           email = "daniel.noble@anu.edu.au",
           role  = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Pieter A.", "Arnold", role = "aut"),
    person("Patrice", "Pottier",
           email = "patrice.pottier@bioenv.gu.se",
           role  = "aut"))
Description: A function library for fitting joint Bayesian four-parameter
    logistic (4PL) models to thermal-tolerance proportion data, extracting
    the classical thermal load sensitivity quantities (z, CTmax at 1 hour,
    T_crit) with full posterior uncertainty, and predicting heat-injury
    accumulation and survival under fluctuating temperature regimes with
    optional Sharpe-Schoolfield repair. Implements the framework described
    in Noble, Arnold and Pottier (in preparation).
